Doc: The specification of whether a barrier within an FX OTC option is a knockin or knockout.

Source.Contents:
/#
 The specification of whether a barrier within an FX OTC option is a knockin or knockout.
 #/
enum FpML5.confirmation.FxBarrierTypeEnum {
    # The option exists if the spot rate is at or above, or at or below the barrier level according to the specified barrier direction.
    Knockin 
    # The option ceases to exist if the spot rate is at or above, or at or below the barrier level according to the specified barrier direction.
    Knockout 
    # DEPRECATE: Option exists once the barrier is hit. The trigger rate is in-the money in relation to the strike rate.
    ReverseKnockin 
    # DEPRECATE: Option ceases to exist once the barrier is hit. The trigger rate is in-the money in relation to the strike rate.
    ReverseKnockout 

}

Knockin.Doc: The option exists if the spot rate is at or above, or at or below the barrier level according to the specified barrier direction.
Knockin.Name: Knockin

Knockout.Doc: The option ceases to exist if the spot rate is at or above, or at or below the barrier level according to the specified barrier direction.
Knockout.Name: Knockout

ReverseKnockin.Doc: DEPRECATE: Option exists once the barrier is hit. The trigger rate is in-the money in relation to the strike rate.
ReverseKnockin.Name: ReverseKnockin

ReverseKnockout.Doc: DEPRECATE: Option ceases to exist once the barrier is hit. The trigger rate is in-the money in relation to the strike rate.
ReverseKnockout.Name: ReverseKnockout
